    "description": "<p>When you cast an offensive spell (@ICON[offensive]) targeting a <strong>single creature</strong>, if the spell has a <strong>total Mind Point cost of 【SL × 20】 or lower</strong>, you may choose one <strong>non-arcane</strong> weapon you have equipped. If you do, your Magic Check for the spell uses the chosen weapon’s Accuracy Check formula; if that formula includes <strong>Dexterity</strong>, the Magic Check also gains a bonus equal to <strong>【SL】.</strong> For instance, casting an Elementalist spell through a <strong>bronze sword</strong> (page <strong>131</strong>) when you have Skill Level 2 in <strong>Spellblade</strong> will cause the Magic Check to be <strong>【DEX + MIG】+3</strong> instead of <strong>【INS + WLP】</strong>.</p>",
